Description: Kazuma's party is suddenly alerted by an outrageous letter delivered by Yunyun. The letter requested that they come to the Crimson Demon Clan's village, that is facing a threat that could mean it's ending.

Name: 371. Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt
Description: During U.C. 0079's One Year War, the Earth Federation and Zeon's Living Dead Division clash fiercely in the Thunderbolt Sector. Ace pilot Lo Flemming gains control of the latest Gundam prototype.

Name: 372. Oban Star-Racers
Description: Earth, 2082, twenty-five years after the failed invasion of the Crog forces. Young Eva (15) is determined to be reunited with her father, race manager Don Wei, who sent her off to a tough boarding school after the tragic death of the mother, ten years earlier. She escapes from school and secretly joins her dad's famous star-racer team under the alias "Molly". But Don Wei doesn't recognize his daughter. He has other troubles on his mind: the President of the Earth Coalition has just put him in charge of a dangerous top-secret mission. Don Wei must lead the Earth to victory in a mysterious and mythical intergalactic competition - The Great Race of Oban. It is said that the outcome of the competition will radically transform the balance of power within our Galaxy. Earth cannot afford to lose - especially not against the Crogs! Before she knows what is happening, "Molly" takes off for the planet Alwas, the first stage of The Great Race of Oban, with Don Wei, champion pilot Rick Thunderbolt, gunner Jordan and mechanics Stan and Koji. The fate of Molly and her friends, as well as the future of the human race, are now inextricably intertwined.

Name: 373. Galaxy Express 999
Description: The adventures of a brave young boy who travels from planet to planet in a determined quest to avenge his mother's death.

Name: 374. Onmyoji
Description: The tale of Abe no Seimei, a legendary spell-caster who lived in ancient Japan.

Name: 375. Tekkonkinkreet
Description: Two boys defend Treasure Town and Yakuza try to take over and clear it for new development.

Name: 376. Digimon Frontier
Description: Five children from the Real World have been called to the Digital World to acquire the "legendary spirits" and save the Digital World from one of the 3 Sacred Angels, Cherubimon, who has rebelled against the other two.

Name: 377. Full Dive: This Ultimate Next-Gen Full Dive RPG Is Even Shittier Than Real Life!
Description: Yuuki Hiroshi has just picked up Kiwame Quest, the most realistic VRMMO of all time. But this RPG is TOO lifelike.

Name: 378. Unnamed Memory
Description: Cursed as a child to never have an heir, Prince Oscar seeks the continent's most powerful witch, Tinasha, hoping she'll break his curse. To meet her, he'll have to climb her formidable tower, which grants a wish to whoever reaches the top.

Name: 379. High Card
Description: The High Card is a secret club of people who own magical playing cards, which specializes in tracking down missing cards and retrieving them.

Name: 380. Macross: Do You Remember Love?
Description: Earth braces for an invasion of giant male bionoids and their enemy, giant female bionoids.

Name: 381. Roujin Z
Description: A compassionate young nurse is determined to help an elderly invalid strapped to a revolutionary health care bed but there are unexpected consequences.

Name: 382. Monster Hunter: Legends of the Guild
Description: In a world where humans and fearsome monsters live in an uneasy balance, young hunter Aiden fights to save his village from destruction by a dragon.

Name: 383. Children of the Whales
Description: As a magic weilder, young archivist Chakuro knows his life will be short, but everything changes when a mysterious girl from the outside arrives on his island.

Name: 384. KamiErabi God.app
Description: Gorou was chosen by a dying god he and other god candidates will kill each other for the title of God and the right to have a wish granted.

Name: 385. Idaten Jump
Description: Sho Yamato and friends get transported to the X-Zone while racing. Trapped, they embark on high-stakes racing adventures, determined to unravel the mystery and find their way home.

Name: 386. Yuuna and the Haunted Hot Springs
Description: A young man with connections to the supernatural rents a room haunted by the ghost of a 16-year-old girl.

Name: 387. Kizumonogatari Part 1: Tekketsu
Description: Follows Araragi's encounter with the vampire Kiss-shot Acerola-orion Heart-under-blade and his journey back into humanity from being a vampire.

Name: 388. Class of '09
Description: After her father commits suicide, a sociopathic girl enrolls into a new American high school in the late 2000's, intending to manipulate and bully her fellow students for status.

Name: 389. Silver Fang
Description: An Akita-Inu puppy is destined to defend his people against a monstrous bear.

Name: 390. Boarding School Juliet
Description: "To Love, or not to Love" Juliet Percia and Inuzuka Romio are archenemies. They lead two high-school dormitories the "Black Dogs" and the "White Cats" from two rivaling countries.

Name: 391. The Magical Revolution of the Reincarnated Princess and the Genius Young Lady
Description: Noblewoman Euphyllia loses her title as heir to the throne. Silly Princess Anisphia secretly plots to restore Euphyllia's honor, unaware their meeting will change the kingdom's fate.

Name: 392. Dakaichi: I'm Being Harassed by the Sexiest Man of the Year-
Description: Saijou Takato's 5 year reign as the 'Most Huggable No. 1' has been snatched. Azumaya is a newbie actor with a 3-year debut, who uses his sincere sparkling smile to blackmail Takato into silence.

Name: 393. Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo
Description: The impossible adventures of Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo, a warrior who fights using his nose hairs to defeat an evil empire that wants to turn the human race bald.

Name: 394. Undead Murder Farce
Description: In a world inhabited by vampires, golems, werewolves and other creatures, Aya Rindo, along with Tsugaru Shunichi and Shizuku Hasei, travels as supernatural detective, solving mysteries while she looks for her lost body.

Name: 395. Her Blue Sky
Description: Second-year high school student Aoi Aioi is an aspiring musician. Her older sister Akane's ex-boyfriend Shinnosuke Kanomura is a struggling guitarist. Aoi and Akane's parents passed away in an accident 13 years ago, and Akane gave up her ambition of going to Tokyo with Shinnosuke to take care of Aoi. Since then, Aoi has felt indebted to her older sister. One day, she is invited to perform at a music festival as a session musician by a famous en singer named Dankichi. At the same time, Shinnosuke returns to Aoi and Akane's town after a long time away. Then, Shinno mysteriously appears- who is actually Shinnosuke from 13 years ago after traveling from the past to the present-and Aoi falls in love for the first time.

Name: 396. Revenger
Description: A vengeful samurai works with a mysterious organization to take revenge on behalf of those who have no power.

Name: 397. Mysterious Girlfriend X
Description: A newly transferred girl to Akira's school happens to drool on the desk. The otherwise normal Akira decides to taste it and it is now that things start to change as he will start going out with the girl, Mikoto, whom he seems destined for.

Name: 398. Villainess Level 99: I May Be the Hidden Boss but I'm Not the Demon Lord
Description: Despite wanting a quiet reborn life, this former college girl levels up to the max as the villainess.

Name: 399. Astro Boy
Description: As long as trouble's brewing across the universe, the small but powerful robot, Astro Boy, will have adventures, assisted by his mentor, Dr. Elefun.

Name: 400. Medabots
Description: 10-year-old Ikki Tenrio has always dreamed about becoming a top-ranked medafighter, and now that he has his own medabot he can finally pursue his dream.

Name: 401. Metallic Rouge
Description: Follows Rouge, an android girl, who is on a mission on Mars with her partner Naomi. The mission is to murder Immortal Nine, nine artificial humans who are hostile to the government.

Name: 402. Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ
Description: Following the decisive battle against the Titans, AEUG's Argama crew (along with a new bunch of kids), has little time to regroup as a new threat looms in the horizon: Haman's Neo Zeon.

Name: 403. My Unique Skill Makes Me OP Even at Level 1
Description: Ry√¥ta Sat√¥ was reincarnated to another world, but he was burdened which his level is fixed to 1 in another world. Although he wasn't able to raise his level, he had a skill to create a cheat-like item that shouldn't exist from monsters.

Name: 404. The Saint's Magic Power Is Omnipotent
Description: Sei is living her dream life in a magical kingdom. She's popular for making potions, but will this obsession hurt her chances with Albert?

Name: 405. Josee, the Tiger and the Fish
Description: Josee suffers from cerebral palsy and has spent her entire life insulated from the outside world by her eccentric overprotective grandmother. One day, she happens to meet Tsuneo, a college student, who gradually becomes attracted to her.

Name: 406. The Asterisk War
Description: The Academy City on water, Rikka is world's largest stage for integrated battle entertainment.

Name: 407. The Magical Girl and the Evil Lieutenant Used to Be Archenemies
Description: The strategist of an evil organization falls for the magical girl fighting against the organization.

Name: 408. Les Miserables: Shoujo Cosette
Description: Cosette, daughter of the unfortunate Fantine, suffers under the cruel Th√©nardiers. Jean Valjean, a former convict disguised as Monsieur Madeleine, seeks redemption while Inspector Javert pursues him.

Name: 409. Mahoutsukai Reimeiki
Description: A magician with zero magic is sent to investigate attacks on magicians, and uncovers a great mystery.

Name: 410. Astro Boy
Description: Originally intended to be kept a secret, the Pinocchio-like character becomes a publicly renowned superhero -- complete with devices like laser-firing fingers, uncanny hearing, and jet-powered boots -- all eventually used to repulse an alien invasion of Earth.

Name: 411. Stand by Me Doraemon
Description: What will happen to Nobita's life after Doraemon leaves?

Name: 412. Pok√©mon the Movie: The Power of Us
Description: Ash meets five residents who come together to save the day when a series of threats endanger the annual Wind Festival and the entire population of their home, Fula City

Name: 413. Free!
Description: Four high school students: Haruka, Makoto, Nagisa and Rin, all took part in a swimming tournament shortly before the end of high school and then lost touch with each other. Years later, they reunite.

Name: 414. Recovery of an MMO Junkie
Description: A stressed office worker quits her job and begins spending all her time playing an online video game, becoming part of a tight-knit friend group that helps her rediscover the joy of living in the real world.

Name: 415. Wandering Witch: The Journey of Elaina
Description: Elaina ventures out to see the world, eager to experience humanity as exploration and curiosity drive her journey. Where to next?.

Name: 416. Dragonaut: The Resonance
Description: With a deadly asteroid hurtling towards Earth, sexy human Dragonauts in tight uniforms and their curvaceous dragon companions come together to create a formidable fighting force with all the right moves. Caught in the middle of this race against time are Jin - a heartbroken young flyboy, and Toa - a voluptuous mystery woman with an amazing set of intergalactic battle skills. Jin's down about the fate of his doomed planet, but Toa is quick to grab him by the seat of his pants and lift his sagging spirits. If these star-crossed space cadets can unlock the secrets of their mysterious connection and convince the Dragonauts to join the action, there may yet be hope for planet Earth!

Name: 417. Tonari no Seki-kun: The Master of Killing Time
Description: In the middle of class at a certain school, a diligent student, has her in-class life turned upside-down when her next-door desk mate "Seki" creates intricate activities to play at his desk during class.

Name: 418. Trigun: Badlands Rumble
Description: 20 years after meddling into the bank heist of a notorious robber named Gasback, Vash the Stampede is heading towards Macca City. Rumors say that the legendary thief might appear there causing an enormous influx of bounty hunters in the area who want to collect the $300,000,000 prize for his head.

Name: 419. Love of Kill
Description: Two assassins are romantically drawn to each other, even though their profession makes them rivals and targets to each other.

Name: 420. The Vexations of a Shut-In Vampire Princess
Description: Komari lives in seclusion, tormented by her inability to drink blood despite being a vampire, her inability to use magic, her inability to exercise and her inability to grow.

Name: 421. Love Me, Love Me Not
Description: The love affairs of four schoolkids: a romantic, a pragmatist, an airhead and a lothario.

Name: 422. O Maidens in Your Savage Season
Description: Girls in a high school literature club answer the question "What's one thing you want to do before you die" with sex, leading to a whirlwind of emotions.

Name: 423. Pok√©mon Chronicles
Description: Various adventures of Trainers in the amazing world Pok√©mon.

Name: 424. Koikimo
Description: A total womanizer and handsome man, and a high school nerdy girl. She saves his life once, he falls for her, becoming her stalker. They do not match, but what will happen between them?

Name: 425. Reign of the Seven Spellblades
Description: Follows Oliver Horn as he enters a prestigious magic school named Kimberly. He discovers that not everything is as it seems, with the emergence of labyrinths, monsters, and other threats that endanger the students.

Name: 426. Engage Kiss
Description: Bayron City is a Mega-Float city in the Pacific Ocean; Shu is a young man living in the city who runs a Private Military Company being supported by the demon Kisara.

Name: 427. Eden
Description: A human girl secretly raised by robots starts to uncover the dark secrets behind her lush, utopian world where humanity has all but vanished.

Name: 428. Hikaru no Go
Description: A sixth-grader Hikaru Shindo accidentally awakens the spirit of a deceased Go prodigy Fujiwara no Sai who then accompanies Hikaru and helps him develop his Go skills.

Name: 429. Because I Don't Like My Big Brother at All!
Description: Second-year middle schooler Nao Takanashi loves her older brother Shuusuke to the point where she has developed a brother complex. Wanting her brother to see her as a woman, Nao makes advances toward him on a daily basis, which often results in Shuusuke succumbing to and encouraging more of her teasing. One day, while throwing away porn magazines from her brother's room, Nao finds an album containing his childhood photos-none of which include her. Having discovered the truth behind her family relationships, Nao becomes ever more affectionate toward Shuusuke. However, it does not take long for her dreams of monopolizing her brother to be put in jeopardy.

Name: 430. The Faraway Paladin
Description: A knight raised by three righteous but monstrous guardians sets out on a quest to improve his land.

Name: 431. Appleseed: Ex Machina
Description: With Brialeos convalescing after a mission, Deunan is assigned a new and remarkably familiar partner as a strange wave of terrorist attacks plague Olympus.

Name: 432. Doraemon the Movie: Nobita's Dinosaur
Description: After bringing a fossilized egg back to life with the Time Cloth, Nobita finds himself the owner of a baby dinosaur. Everything is fine until it grows up. Nobita and friends use Doraemon's time machine to return it back to its own time.

Name: 433. Colorful
Description: A sinful spirit is granted the opportunity to prove worthy for rebirth, inhabiting the body of a student who killed himself.

Name: 434. Hensuki: Are you willing to fall in love with a pervert, as long as she's a cutie?
Description: A mysterious love letter winds up in Keiki's locker with a pair of white panties! Will he be able to find the panty-leaving-Cinderella?

Name: 435. Tearmoon Empire
Description: A selfish princess wakes up back in time after her own execution and gets a second chance to rebuild her empire and prevent her own death.

Name: 436. Mega Man
Description: Based on the video game series, the robot Mega Man and his dog Rush battle the creations of his father, the scientist Dr. Light, who were corrupted by Light's former partner Dr. Wily and his minions, in an attempt to take over the world.

Name: 437. Mischievous Kiss
Description: A cute girl (Aihara Kotoko) is in love with a smart and handsome guy who's a jerk in high school (Irie Naoki) and when her house is destroyed she moves with her father in to the Irie Family home where he starts to develop some feelings towards her.

Name: 438. OniAi
Description: After 6 years of living apart due to the death of their parents, the Himenokoji twins, Akito and Akiko, are finally reunited when Akito desires to live as a family once more. Although things are fine at first, Akiko begins to express her incestuous love for her older brother, who only sees her as his little sister.

Name: 439. Princess Connect! Re: Dive
Description: After falling from the sky with no memories of his past, Yuuki forms an alliance with 3 new friends, and the hidden mysteries surrounding him and his allies begin to be revealed.

Name: 440. The 8th Son? Are You Kidding Me?
Description: Shingo Ichinomiya, a 25-year-old man working at a firm company reincarnated as the youngest child of a poor noble family living in a back country. He is blessed with a very rare talent, but in his situation it only brought disaster.

Name: 441. The Kingdom of Dreams and Madness
Description: Follows the routines of those employed at Studio Ghibli, including filmmakers Hayao Miyazaki, Isao Takahata, and Toshio Suzuki as they work to release two films simultaneously, The Wind Rises and The Tale of the Princess Kaguya.

Name: 442. The Concierge at Hokkyoku Department Store
Description: Akino, the new concierge works at a mysterious department store where a majority of the customers are animals.

Name: 443. Sword Art Online the Movie: Ordinal Scale
Description: Kirito uncovers a conspiracy within Ordinal Scale, a popular AR game developed for a new system called The Augma.

Name: 444. The Deer King
Description: The last survivor of a band of warriors is enslaved in a salt mine. One night, savage dogs attack and a mysterious disease wipes out everyone at the mine. The warrior escapes with a little girl, while a gifted physician looks for a cure.

Name: 445. Dusk Maiden of Amnesia
Description: Niija Teiichi, a freshman, discovers a haunted school building where he encounters a ghost. He helps the ghost investigate her mysterious death.

Name: 446. Appleseed
Description: In a utopian society created at the end of the third world war, a female warrior who has been plucked from the badlands begins to see cracks in this new facade. And what does this community have planned for the rest of humankind?

Name: 447. NiNoKuni
Description: High school peers Yuu and Haru travel between the real world and a parallel fantasy universe to help their friend Kotona, whose life is in danger.

Name: 448. The Comic Artist and Assistants
Description: A hilarious slice of life comedy that leisurely depicts the day-to-day life of manga artist Aito Yuuki and his assistant, Ashisu Sahoto.

Name: 449. Back Street Girls
Description: Three gangsters are forced by their boss into becoming a trio of pop singers.

Name: 450. Sasaki and Peeps
Description: Sasaki, an office worker, buys a bird that can actually give him supernatural powers to cross between worlds. Although he wants to use that power to live in peace, there are various characters who may get in the way of his wishes.

Name: 451. Made in Abyss: Journey's Dawn
Description: A girl named, Riko and her robot friend, Reg, journey down into a deadly, otherworldly chasm, known as the Abyss, in search of her lost mother.

Name: 452. Oni: Thunder God's Tale
Description: In a mystical world of Japanese gods and spirits, a courageous girl strives to follow in her mysterious father's footsteps and find her true powers.

Name: 453. White Snake
Description: A love story between a snake spirit and a snake hunter.

Name: 454. Dark Gathering
Description: A withdrawn college kid with psychic powers teams up with a strange little girl who's searching for her dead mother's abducted soul.

Name: 455. Protocol: Rain
Description: After his father was killed in an accident and his sister was injured, Shun Tokinoya works at an esports cafe. While the cafe is in debt, he and his friends hope to win the "Xaxerion Championship" in order to repay their debts.

Name: 456. Cat Soup
Description: A young anthropomorphic cat goes on a psychedelic journey with his sister in order to save her soul.

Name: 457. Okko's Inn
Description: After losing her parents in a car accident, Okko starts living in the countryside with her grandmother who runs a traditional Japanese inn. While she prepares to be the next owner of the inn, Okko can somehow see friendly ghosts.

Name: 458. After-school Hanako-kun
Description: When not preserving harmony between the living and spirit realms, Hanako-kun and his human assistant Nene Yashiro, a first-year student at Kamome Academy, fill their time with other activities.

Name: 459. Magical Sempai
Description: Starting his new term at Tanenashi High School, an unmotivated freshman searches for a club that requires minimal participation to suit his needs. He then comes across the magic clubroom, and inside is a cute upperclassman practicing her magic tricks. Suffering from stage fright that causes her to slip up in her acts, she has a tendency to end up in the most embarrassing situations. Despite having little interest in a club run by an incapable magician, the freshman finds himself involved as a new member, experiencing all sorts of awkward moments with his eccentric mentor.

Name: 460. Shakugan No Shana
Description: Yuji is returning from school when suddenly time stops and monsters appear to devour people. He is not frozen, however. When one of the monsters spots him, he is saved by Shana, the great equalizer, who tells him he's a fading spirit.

Name: 461. The Dungeon of Black Company
Description: In debt and in a new world? Kinji's living a nightmare. Avoiding work is gonna be a tough grind. Does he have what it takes?

Name: 462. Didn't I Say to Make My Abilities Average in the Next Life?!
Description: When she turns ten years old, Adele von Ascham is hit with a horrible headache-and memories of her previous life as an eighteen-year-old Japanese girl named Kurihara Misato.

Name: 463. Tachibanakan Triangle
Description: High school student Natsuno Hanabi moves into a dorm full of strange characters, including a childhood friend who's in love with her and a mysterious girl that Hanabi's slowly falling for.

Name: 464. Senpai is an Otokonoko
Description: Makoto Hanaoka, a high school student who practices crossdressing. Saki, another high school student, confesses her feelings to Makoto, who reveals his secret to her.

Name: 465. The Detective Is Already Dead
Description: A detective's assistant risks opening old wounds when he stumbles into a new case threading murder, global conspiracy, and his dead partner!.

Name: 466. Maoyu ~ Archenemy & Hero
Description: When Hero discovers that the Demon King is not what he expected, the two begin to strike a deal that could save the world.

Name: 467. I Want You to Show Me Your Panties with a Disgusted Face
Description: A project where a number of women in different costumes show their panties while they make a disgusted face.

Name: 468. I've Been Killing Slimes for 300 Years and Maxed Out My Level
Description: Azusa Aizawa, a 27 years old woman, died on work site due to overworking. She has the possibility to reincarnate, and so she plans to live a chilling and calm life. But will she be able to be relaxed?

Name: 469. My Stepmom's Daughter Is My Ex
Description: Former couple Mizuto and Yume reunite as step-siblings when their parents announce a marriage on the day before high school. To prioritize their parents' relationship, they establish a rule to not engage in any sexual activities.

Name: 470. Blend S
Description: Sakuranomiya Maika is, by nature, a person with bad luck who always gets into trouble, but knows Dino, who manages a cafe. However, it is not any cafe, as the waitresses have to act according to their "attributes."

Name: 471. Gundam Build Fighters
Description: In a world where Gundam is a very popular T.V. show, Sei Iori wishes to be just like his father, who was a Gunpla champion years ago, unfortunately, Sei only has skill in building Gunpla, but once he meets a boy named Reiji, who has the ability to fight with his Gunpla, everything changes. Will they be able to make it to the top just like his father did?

Name: 472. Hula Fulla Dance
Description: A young girl joins the Spa Resort Hawaiians hotel to serve as a hula dancer.

Name: 473. Time of Eve
Description: In a not too distant future, a young man's outlook on his home android begins to change after tracking the android's behavioral log to a mysterious cafe.

Name: 474. Astro Boy
Description: Starring Astro, Japan's first Superhero and a modern folk hero- an anime adaption for the new century based on the seminal manga 'Astro Boy' by the 'God of Manga' Osamu Tezuka.

Name: 475. Digimon Tamers
Description: An animated series based on the popular children's toy "Digimon", in which kids raise electronic monsters to fight against those raised by other kids.

Name: 476. Thermae Romae Novae
Description: The Roman architect Lucius is transported through time to modern-day Japan, where he learns about Japanese bathhouses and uses this to his gain back home.

Name: 477. Modest Heroes
Description: An anthology of three original shorts written and directed by Hiromasa Yonebayashi, Yoshiyuki Momose and Akihiko Yamashita.

Name: 478. King's Game
Description: A class of high school students receive a text message welcoming them to a game where they are given tasks they must complete in 24 hours.

Name: 479. Arknights: Prelude to Dawn
Description: In the land of Terra, natural disasters of unknown causes have been occurring irregularly in many areas. Therefore, the majority of the people, in order to escape those natural disasters, came to live in mobile cities developed over the years. The Originium left behind at the site of such Catastrophes, has led to the rapid progress of civilization due to their immense energy. But it also brought something else with it - an incurable disease called Oripathy. Because the bodies of those with Oripathy gradually crystallize and become a new source of infection at the time of death, in many countries, the Infected are subject to persecution under regimes of segregation and forced labor. Those who were oppressed by the governments are starting to rebel. Rhodes Island, a pharmaceutical company researching a cure for Oripathy, takes up their arms and starts a conquest trying to save all the people from the disease.

Name: 480. Ultramarine Magmell
Description: Unknown creatures. Deadly pitfalls. With so many reckless adventures out to make fortune, someone's got to rescue them.

Name: 481. Boys Over Flowers
Description: A hard-working middle-class student at a prestigious school finds herself involved in the lives of four infamous bullies.

Name: 482. The Mouse and His Child
Description: Adaptation of Russell Hoban's novel about two mechanical toy mice, and their quest to become "self-winding".

Name: 483. Kase-san and Morning Glories
Description: Yamada is a shy girl in high school who loves doing greenery committee work, but one day she falls into conversation with kase-san the popular and talented school track star. Suddenly Yamada's whole life changes and she realises she likes kase-san. But how can yamada admit het feelings for another girl and could kase-san ever fall in love with her too?

Name: 484. Sabikui Bisco
Description: In a world where mushrooms have decimated the people of earth, a doctor gets caught up in a conflict between the survivors' government and a band of revolutionaries.

Name: 485. The Anthem of the Heart
Description: A young girl had her voice magically taken away so that she would never hurt people with it, but her outlook changes when she encounters music and friendship.

Name: 486. Genius Party
Description: Several directors take part in an anthology dedicated to short anime films.

Name: 487. I'm Giving the Disgraced Noble Lady I Rescued a Crash Course in Naughtiness
Description: When a dark lord finds an abandoned and unhappy noblewoman in his forest, he takes her in and decides to spice up her life with naughty deeds.

Name: 488. Urusei Yatsura 2: Beautiful Dreamer
Description: The night before the school festival, things seem to be repeating themselves. Gradually, all the world functions come to a stop, the only ones that are not affected are a select group of student friends.

Name: 489. Poupelle of Chimney Town
Description: A factory town is covered by chimney smoke, and as the townspeople haven't see the sky in centuries, they no longer believe that stars exist. A chimney sweep and a friendly monster named Poupelle decide to prove that stars are real.

Name: 490. Ground Control to Psychoelectric Girl
Description: Makoto Niwa moves in with his eccentric aunt and cousin. As it so happens, his cousin believes herself to be an alien. Makoto takes it upon himself to reintroduce her to society.

Name: 491. Mardock Scramble: The First Compression
Description: In a futuristic society, a 15-year-old prostitute named Rune Balot is rescued after being nearly killed. She is subconsciously given the choice to continue living due to an emergency ordinance to preserve life called Mardock Scramble 09. Turned into a cyborg, Balot is then given the choice of assisting the investigations against the man who tried to terminate her. He is part of the powerful October corporation that is stealthily conducting illegal activities.

Name: 492. BlackedTheAnime
Description: Herroshiman befriends a 37 year old man named Greg and together they go on peril journeys and discover the truth of what the meaning of friendship really is.

Name: 493. Vandread
Description: In a space-fairing future the war between sexes becomes literal. A kid who works in a factory that produces giant military robots decides to steal one for himself and ends up in the middle of a dogfight that leads into an adventure.

Name: 494. My Sister, My Writer
Description: Sibling duo Suzuka and Nagami collaborate on a light novel. Suzuka writes it, but due to societal pressures, her brother Nagami publishes it under a pen name, kick starting his proxy novelist career.

Name: 495. Do You Love Your Mom and Her Two-Hit Multi-Target Attacks?
Description: Masato is transported into a video game world for the adventure of a lifetime. The only catch? His mom's joining his party.

Name: 496. Alien: Monday
Description: The crew of the Thanatos, a remote mining ship at the edge of the galaxy, discover the danger of an uninvited cargo.

Name: 497. Loveless
Description: Twelve year old Aoyagi Ritsuka is left with his insane mother as his only family when his brother, Seimei, is killed suddenly. After moving to a new school, he meets Agatsuma Soubi, who claims to have known his brother. Ritsuka discovers that Soubi and Seimei used to be a fighting pair, whereby Soubi was the "Fighter" and Seimei was the "Sacrifice". Now that Seimei is gone, Ritsuka has inherited Soubi, who will become his "Fighter". After learning that Seimei was killed by an organization known as the "Seven Moons", Ritsuka decides to investigate into his brother's death, with the sometimes useless help of Soubi, along the way.

Name: 498. Giovanni's Island
Description: A dramatic yet heart-warming story of cross-cultural friendship among children in the aftermath of WWII, presented by Tokyo-based award-winning animation studio Production I.G. Based on true events.

Name: 499. Oni
Description: A highly trained woman named Konoko has a mission she must complete to defeat the evil Syndicate. Use machine guns and other weapons as you try to uncover her past.

Name: 500. Sing "Yesterday" for Me
Description: A college graduate with no ambition or dreams leads a meaningless life, but the arrival of possible romantic interests may give him hope.

Name: 501. Brothers Conflict
Description: After Ema's dad decides to marry a woman by the name of Miwa Asahina, Ema discovers that she has thirteen step brothers!

Name: 502. The Most Heretical Last Boss Queen: From Villainess to Savior
Description: A girl is reborn as the villainess of a fantasy game she once played, and now seeks to avoid her doom by carrying out heroic deeds.

Name: 503. Descending Stories: Showa Genroku Rakugo Shinju
Description: Now a rakugo artist himself, Yotarou is challenged to keep the art form alive, meanwhile witnessing the final years of his master, Yakumo.

Name: 504. Dragon Crisis!
Description: A normal high school boy Ryuji Kisaragi's peaceful life is turned into an adventure by the return of his second cousin, Eriko. Ryuji and Eriko seize a relic box from a black broker named FANG. In the box, they find a red dragon girl whom Ryuji names Rose because of her rose like pattern on her left hand. In order to protect Rose from the black organization, Ryuji decides to fight using his power as a relic handler.

Name: 505. Accel World
Description: Haruyuki is an overweight kid and at bottom of food chain at his middle school. Within sci-fi setting of real world he often seeks refuge in a virtual one.

Name: 506. Terminator Salvation: The Machinima Series
Description: Blair Williams is fighting the war against the machines in downtown Los Angeles while tracking down the infamous hacker "the ghost" and trying to pursue him to join sides with the resistance.

Name: 507. Gabriel and the Guardians
Description: Gabriel and the Guardians is an epic anime fantasy that tells the journey of Gabriel, a Celestial being from an unseen realm, who collides with mortals and dark giants in a battle for destiny and light.

Name: 508. Horus: Prince of the Sun
Description: A boy with a mythical sword wants to protect a Norse village from an evil ice wizard and his minions, who destroyed his family's village. However, the villagers don't fully trust him and a mysterious girl with a dark secret befriends him.

Name: 509. Summoned to Another World for a Second Time
Description: Slightly gloomy teen Setsu is summoned to another world to save them, but wait, this isn't his first time doing it. Five years in the alternative world of Eclair have passed since the hero came to end the war and brought peace. However, a trap sent him back to his original world as a baby with his memories and powers intact. War's threatening the land again, but this hero is ready for round two.

Name: 510. Photon
Description: A young man with super-strength leaves his home to find a missing friend. He accidentally gets engaged to a runaway pilot as they flee the evil galactic emperor's henchmen, facing cooking contests, exploding spas, and alien cheerleaders.

Name: 511. Revolutionary Girl Utena: The Movie
Description: Utena Tenjou disguises herself as a boy for the Ohtori Academy, however she encounters trouble due to a ring which shows she's skilled duelist. As well as this, the vice president of the school challenges her to a duel

Name: 512. Tsuredure Children
Description: A series of stories, some loosely connected to each other, about young male and female highschool students struggling to confess their feelings to each other.

Name: 513. A Dog's Courage
Description: Stray dogs who have been abandoned by humans find "a place without humans" and realize their identities and the meaning of freedom and self-identity.

Name: 514. Marvel vs. Capcom 2: New Age of Heroes
Description: A pirate-woman named Ruby-Heart who united fifty-two of the Earth's strongest heroes and villains, transports them to another dimension on her enormous battleship to fight an evil shape-shifter named Abyss who wants to rule all realities.

Name: 515. Malevolent Spirits: Mononogatari
Description: Raging after a tragic encounter with tsukumogami, Kunato joins Nagatsuki's clan that uses divine powers to send the spirits back. Nagatsuki's positive experience with tsukumogami contrasts Kunato's loss. Can she change his view?

Name: 516. Master Keaton
Description: Taichi Keaton is a half-British half-Japanese archaeologist and SAS veteran of the Falklands War. He solves mysteries and investigates insurance fraud for Lloyd's around the world.

Name: 517. Ghost in the Shell: SAC_2045 - Sustainable War
Description: In the year 2045, cybernetic mercenary Motoko Kusanagi returns to Section 9 to face a dangerous new threat: the posthumans. A feature-length recut of the first season of Ghost in the Shell: SAC_2045.

Name: 518. Helck
Description: A human enters a tournament of demons to become the king of demons.

Name: 519. Ya Boy Kongming!
Description: A military hero of the Three Kingdoms era is reincarnated in Shibuya and becomes a legend among its party people while devoting himself to peace.

Name: 520. The Princess and the Pilot
Description: A pilot, despite being advised not to, bonds with a princess when he is tasked with escorting the royal subject overseas and across enemy territory to reunite her with her future husband.

Name: 521. Sasaki and Miyano: Graduation chapter
Description: The school year is coming to a close, and Sasaki's graduation draws near. He and Miyano have only a brief amount of time left to enjoy being in school together, and they want to take every opportunity to do just that.

Name: 522. Puppet Princess
Description: A family who builds special karakuri puppets is slain by an evil warlord. But one member, the princess, survives, and uses her skill with puppets to go on a quest for vengeance.

Name: 523. Child of Kamiari Month
Description: A year after losing her mother, a little girl learns that she must journey across Japan to the annual gathering of gods in the sacred land of Izumo.

Name: 524. Play it Cool, Guys
Description: A slice of life comedy about cool but secretly clumsy guys.

Name: 525. Arcadia of My Youth
Description: Space captain Harlock, the latest in a family of proud aerial warriors, begins his journey to free the oppressed Earth from the despotic Illumidas Command.

Name: 526. Vexille
Description: Japan, 2077: A female agent named Vexille is dispatched to Tokyo to investigate whether Japanese are developing robotic technology, which has been banned by the U.N. due to its potential threat to humankind.

Name: 527. Dragons of Wonderhatch
Description: Nagi, a high school girl in the real world, and Tyme, a boy who lives in another world where dragonriders hear the cries of dragons and communicate with them.

Name: 528. Majikoi ~ Oh! Samurai Girls
Description: In Kawakami City, having a samurai ancestor and 'fighting spirit' isn't just an interesting fact, it dictates how you're ranked on the social totem pole. Fortunately, that's something kids like Yamato Naoe have learned to deal with by forming into small 'bands,' (that's the samurai type, NOT music.) However, the delicate balance of Yamato's group is thrown off when two more girls join the group.

Name: 529. BUCCHIGIRI?!
Description: Araji Tomobishi gets caught up in battles among powerful individuals after reuniting with his former friend Mataka Asamine. Meanwhile, the shadow of a colossal demon appears...?!.

Name: 530. Assassin(s)
Description: Old professional killer Wagner seeks someone to teach what he knows as long as he is already dying, and he chooses Max, young and passionless thief to be his successor.

Name: 531. Dance with Devils
Description: Second-year student Ritsuka Tachibana has the perfect school-to-life balance, but all of that's thrown into chaos when she discovers that several of her handsome male classmates are actually demons in disguise.

Name: 532. The Marginal Service
Description: A group of public safety workers secretly work to protect the world from aliens.

Name: 533. Cardfight!! Vanguard
Description: There are now billions of card game players in the world, to an extent where card games have become a necessity, a part of our lives.

Name: 534. Black Cat
Description: Train Heartnet is a famous assassin known as Black Cat. He works for Chronos, an organization that secretly controls the world.

Name: 535. Teknoman
Description: In futuristic 2300 AD, alien invaders called Radam attack Earth. Months later, a powerful warrior named Blade emerges to fight them alongside the Space Knights. However, Blade harbors secrets about his past.

Name: 536. Fluffy Paradise
Description: Akitsu Midori (27 years old), ends up in another world after dying from overwork?. I got reincarnated in another world after God blessed me with a special ability. This ability is "to be loved by non-human beings.

Name: 537. Little Witch Academia
Description: Inspired by a magician named Shiny Chariot, the lively Akko Kagari enters the Little Witch Academy with the dream of one day becoming as cool and great as her idol.

Name: 538. Burst Angel
Description: In a chaotic future Tokyo, a young aspiring chef is employed by four beautiful mercenaries.

Name: 539. Pui Pui Molcar
Description: Pui Pui Molcar centers in the wonderful soft world where cars are guinea pigs and humans are occasionally plastic dolls. This stop-motion animated short series brings all you ever wanted in a TV show to life.

Name: 540. The Prince of Tennis II: U-17 WORLD CUP SEMIFINAL
Description: After the quarterfinals, the U-17 World Cup Team Japan's quest for international glory is the nine-time tournament champion, Germany pro player Jurgen Borisovich Volk next. Trying to reach the finals for the first time in Japan's tennis history. We see Japan vs Germany and Spain vs USA in this Semifinal.

Name: 541. Konohana Kitan
Description: A fox girl starts working at a hot spring inn for spirits.

Name: 542. Mezzo DSA
Description: Mikura and her friends are back for more danger then ever in these thirteen action packed episodes.

Name: 543. Crush Crush
Description: Hey hot stuff. Are you looking for a fun and flirty game to kill some time and make you laugh out loud? That's a crazy coincidence, because it's been looking for you. Welcome to Crush Crush - the Idle Dating Sim.

Name: 544. Armitage III: Dual Matrix
Description: Five years after the OAV series, Third series robot Naomi Armitage and her husband Ross Sylibus now live peacefully on Mars with their daughter, until a corporation wants to know the secrets of the third's ability to bear children.

Name: 545. Akebi's Sailor Uniform
Description: Komichi Akebi is starting junior high at the prestigious Robai Academy in the countryside. It's been her dream to wear a sailor-style school uniform and tomorrow her dream will come true.

Name: 546. Azur Lane: Slow Ahead!
Description: This is a slightly peculiar world where the shipgirls live in. A lively and enjoyable school life for girls from different factions will begin at the naval port of Azur Lane. Living out their lives to the fullest, these girls get into various shenanigans--slowly but surely!

Name: 547. Lupin the 3rd vs. Cat's Eye
Description: Lupin III competes with the Kisugi sisters to steal a triptych of paintings that once belonged to their father, and which hold the key to a long-unsolved mystery.

Name: 548. Gold Kingdom and Water Kingdom
Description: Sara and Naranbayar, a princess and young man from either country who meet by chance, and find that they must act as a couple to maintain peace in their realms. Even so, they find that they slowly fall for each other.

Name: 549. The Mirror/Anime
Description: TV Series

Name: 550. Monsuno
Description: Monsuno hurtled through space eons before man existed. Upon burning through the planet's atmosphere and crashing to Earth, it brought chaos and the extinction of the dinosaurs. Then, it vanished. Now, Monsuno is back. Is the Earth doomed?

Name: 551. Hammerhead
Description: A bad man becomes a superhero and goes on a rampage.

Name: 552. Dr. Ramune -Mysterious Disease Specialist-
Description: Ramune, a doctor who acts freely all the time, is badly spoken and doesn't even look like a doctor. He is facing a "mysterious illness" that has no cure. But he is able to discover the cause and cure his patients.

Name: 553. Blush Blush
Description: You are responsible for a curse that befalls 12 unfortunate (hawt) dudes. Now you have to find them and break the curse.

Name: 554. Kimagure Orange Road: I Want to Return to That Day
Description: A follow up to the television series "Kimagure Orange Road" that wraps up loose ends. Kyosuke must deal with the fact that his, Hikaru and Madoka's friendship is falling apart.

Name: 555. The Dog of Flanders
Description: A small poor boy lives with his caring grandfather in a small Flemish village in the 19th century Belgium, has a lovable pet dog, loves art and dreams of becoming a famous painter one day. Based on a famous Flemish novel.

Name: 556. Gensomaden Saiyuki
Description: Demons and man lived together in harmony until a band of rogue demonic forces seek to resurrect a diabolical monster and a dark spiritual power covered the land. Demons no longer see mankind as friend but as food. A group of unlikely allies unite and fight to bring harmony to this dangerous land.

Name: 557. Naruto Shipp√ªden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 3
Description: The game follows the events of the previous game when all the five Kages gather to the land of iron to discuss how to deal with the Akatsuki. But the summit is soon attacked by Sasuke Uchiha who is after Danzo the new Hokage.

Name: 558. Flaming Alpine Rose: Jeudi & Lundi
Description: Young Lundi finds an amnesiac girl, names her Jeudi. A Count kidnaps her, mistaking her for a past love. Lundi rescues Jeudi and they seek her identity, aided by Leonhardt, while evading the Count and Nazis during WWII.

Name: 559. Engine Sentai Go-onger
Description: Six giant vehicular beings called Engines chase down three Pollution Ministers' from the Barbaric Machine Clan Gaiark from the Engine's home world to Earth. The six Engines manage to pursue them, selecting five humans to become their partners, the Go-ongers. The team are joined by Go-on Wings and their Wing Engines, as well as the Ancient Engines, as they all together battle the Gaiark as well as other evil villains from other Braneworlds.

Name: 560. Amagi Brilliant Park
Description: The film is set in an amusement park in the Tokyo suburbs of Japan, with a princess at the center of the story.

Name: 561. I Shall Survive Using Potions!
Description: Join Nagase Kaoru, a reincarnated office lady, as she navigates a new world using her knowledge and cleverness to thrive and survive in this exciting adventure!

Name: 562. Gekijouban Toaru majutsu no indekkusu: Endyumion no kiseki
Description: In a futuristic metropolis full of super-powered students, Kamijo, Index and their allies use sorcery and science to keep Arisa, a level 0 girl, safe.

Name: 563. Iwakakeru -Sport Climbing Girls-
Description: Konomi Kasahara, a junior high school girl, has made a big name after winning numerous competitive puzzle game tournaments. The story begins when she finds a sports climbing club in her high school. Using special skills other than that of puzzle games, Konomi becomes fascinated with climbing.

Name: 564. Air Gear
Description: A couple of orphans form a gang called Storm Riders and try to become top dogs in the competitive world of professional and street sport that involves Air Treks, futuristic motorized rollerblades that can achieve super speed.

Name: 565. Dear Brother
Description: Sixteen-year-old Nanako Misonoo deals with high school drama and gossip at her prestigious academy by writing letters to her brother.

Name: 566. Ikebukuro West Gate Park
Description: Follows Makoto Majima and the interactions he has with the gangs that are located in his area of Japan.

Name: 567. A Playthrough of a Certain Dude's VRMMO Life
Description: Daichi Tanaka enjoys playing VRMMO called "One More Free Life Online" in his free time and logs in as a young boy avatar called Earth. He wants to master a skill that's been deemed to be useless.

Name: 568. Space Battleship Yamato
Description: Gamilons are a race of evil aliens that are trying to destroy the planet Earth. However, a group of civilians look to the battleship Yamato for its space travel and go on a mission to bring back a neutralizer that will get rid of the radiation from the Earth.

Name: 569. Pingu in the City
Description: Pingu and his family move from their small village to the big city; in which there are many people with many different occupations. The ever-curious Pingu tries to join them at their jobs, but his mischievous side gets the better of him and he ends up messing things up.

Name: 570. Lagrange: The Flower of Rin-ne
Description: Madoka an energetic school girl is recruited by a mysterious girl called Lan to pilot a robot in order to protect her city from enemies from space with an as of yet unknown goal.

Name: 571. Maria the Virgin Witch
Description: Maria, the most powerful witch who lives during the Hundred Years' War in France. She despises war, so she obstructs battles with her strong magical powers. However not everyone loves her action, including the angel.

Name: 572. Never-Ending Man: Hayao Miyazaki
Description: A look at famous Japanese animator Hayao Miyazaki following his retirement in 2013.

Name: 573. Pet
Description: Hiroki, Tsukasa, and Satoru find themselves enlisted by a shadowy organization that exploits their psychic abilities.

Name: 574. Stop!! Hibari-kun!
Description: Kousaku Sakamoto is a high school student who has to live with Yakuza boss Ibari Oozora and his four(?) daughters as the last wish after the death of his mother. However Hibari turns out to be a trans girl for the surprise of Kousaku.

Name: 575. In The Beginning: The Bible Stories
Description: An anime series based on the Old Testament in the Bible, up until the birth of Jesus Christ.

Name: 576. Spider Riders
Description: A bunch of these guys that ride around on giant arachnids to try and stop that bad guys! The badguys are really evil, and ride scorpions, and the spiders talk!

Name: 577. Bright: Samurai Soul
Description: Izo, a Ronin, and Raiden, an orc, work to bring a young elf girl and the wand she carries to the land of the elves in the north.

Name: 578. Hangyakusei Million Arthur
Description: A squad of avatars of King Arthur are assembled to travel through time and protect history.

Name: 579. Snow Daze
Description: A voiced interactive visual novel. you choose the path forward during the period of a snowed in week. In addition to the main five day story the game includes individual extended endings, character side stories, and blooper reels.

Name: 580. Sweet Blue Flowers
Description: The trials and tribulations of a gang of schoolgirls as they walk through life together.

Name: 581. Barangay 143
Description: Barangay 143 follows the coming of age story of a young man in search of a father and how he finds an unlikely family in a team of misfits trying to bring glory to their hometown. It's a story about love and family set against the action-packed world of street basketball, where the stakes are always high and life is the biggest game you can win.

Name: 582. The Birth of Kitaro: Mystery of GeGeGe
Description: Mizuki visits a village ruled by the Ryuga, with the goal to mourn the now dead head of the family and a secret mission. There he meets Kitaro's father looking for his wife, and together, they have to uncover mysteries of the family.

Name: 583. Macross Plus Movie Edition
Description: Two rival test pilots strive to be the best there is at what they do and also to win the heart of the woman behind the AI pop sensation Sharon Apple. Movie compilation of the acclaimed four-chapter OVA with additional scenes.

Name: 584. Beautiful Bones: Sakurako's Investigation
Description: Shoutarou Tatewaki, a high schooler living in Asahikawa City, Hokkaido, meets Sakurako Kujou, a bone-loving ojou-san who has an ability to analyze specimen. Because of meeting her, he has to accompany her to various cases.

Name: 585. Ayaka: A Story of Bonds and Wounds
Description: As an orphan, Yukito Yanagi's life is filled with questions, but that all changed when he meets his father's disciple who takes him to his birthplace on Ayaka. A strange island filled with legends of dragons and mysterious beings.

Name: 586. Metamorphoses
Description: Several animated stories from "Metamorphoses", Roman poet Ovid's narrative of legends, are presented.

Name: 587. Go Go Anime!
Description: A documentary on anime fans as they wait for Anime Expo 2003.

Name: 588. This Art Club Has a Problem!
Description: An ordinary arts club at an ordinary middle school, Tsukimori Middle School. One member, Uchimaki Subaru, wastes his abundant talent trying to draw his perfect 2D waifu. Another, Usami Mizuki, can't stop thinking about the loser that is Uchimaki-kun. Then there is the club president, who, despite being asleep all the time, seems to care for the two, and another vague, sketchy member, Colette. Today, yet again, in this art club full of mild disappointments, a problem arises.

Name: 589. Air Master
Description: High school girl Maki is secretly an undefeated street fighter known as Air Master. When she defends girls from a bully, another fighter called Lucha Master challenges her to an intense battle.

Name: 590. Future Folktales
Description: In Saudi Arabia, a grandmother keeps her Arabic heritage alive through telling folktales to her grandchildren.

Name: 591. Mai Mai Miracle
Description: Inspired by her grandfather's stories, young Shinko embarks on wild flights of fancy about the history of the little town she lives in. But dreams can't fend off the realities of growing up.

Name: 592. Otherside Picnic
Description: Moments from death, Sorawo is saved by the mysterious Toriko in the world of the Otherside. Entranced by its beauty, she discovers that this dimension is inhabited by monsters once thought imaginary.

Name: 593. MM!
Description: Taro Sado is a masochist and goes to a high school with his male friend Tatsukichi Hayama. Taro falls in love for the first time with a girl and wants to be cured of his masochism so that he can confess his love to her, unaware at the time that she is actually his cross-dressing male friend Tatsukichi, so he goes to the Second Voluntary Club to get help. There he meets Mio Isurugi, a self-proclaimed god, and Arashiko Yuno, the girl who made him a masochist in the first place, however, she has androphobia. The club adviser is the school nurse, Michiru Onigawara. Other characters include Yumi Mamiya, Arashiko's best friend, and the president of the Inventors Club, Noa Hiragi, and her lolicon assistant, Himura Yukinojo.

Name: 594. Arknights: Perish in Frost
Description: TV Series

Name: 595. Aho Girl
Description: The adventures of an idiot girl and her long-suffering friends.

Name: 596. Pole Position
Description: A teen stunt car team secretly fights crime with the help of their artificially intelligent cars.

Name: 597. COLORFUL STAGE! The Movie: A Miku Who Can't Sing
598. Girls Beyond the Wasteland
Description: Buntarou doesn't know what he wants to do in the future. He does not have any kind of dream that he wants to pursue, so currently he just spends his days hanging around with his friends. One day, his classmate Sayuki asks him if he wants to help with development of a gal game. She says that she had become interested in his help after she read one of his works intended for the drama club. Buntarou doesn't know anything about gal games, but Sayuki claims that she has the ability to make it a success. Can they make the game, and will it be a success like she claims it will be? This is the story of youths taking a daring step into the unknown...

Name: 599. Panda and the Magic Serpent
Description: The adventures of a cute little panda, a dragon god and an evil serpent.

Name: 600. Uragiri wa Boku no Namae o Shitteiru
Description: Yuki, an orphan with the ability to feel others' emotions and transfer their pain to himself, seeks answers about his past while struggling to control his dangerous powers with the help of a silver-eyed guardian sworn to protect him.

Name: 601. Arakawa Under the Bridge
Description: A young man is drawn by his eccentric new girlfriend into her home, a village of eccentrics who live under a bridge on the Arakawa River.

Name: 602. Natsume's Book of Friends the Movie: Ephemeral Bond
Description: An orphaned teen encounters a supernatural creature that has the ability to look human.

Name: 603. Izetta: The Last Witch
Description: In 1939 A.D., the imperialist nation of Germany invaded a neighboring country. At once, this war spread across Europe, and the era was dragged into a spiral of a great war.

Name: 604. The Fire Hunter
Description: When a Fire Hunter dies in her presence, Touko must make a treacherous journey to the capital for redemption, and just may change the destiny of the destitute world.

Name: 605. How Clumsy You Are, Miss Ueno.
Description: Ueno-san, who is in her third year of junior high school, is in love with the concept of falling in love. She makes full use of her inventions and tries to show it off to Tanaka, her Science Club junior.

Name: 606. High School Fleet
Description: Living by the sea, protecting the sea, and journeying across the sea, that is the life of the Blue Mermaid, group of women trained to operate navy warships to protect international peace and handling maritime disaster. 15 year old girl, Misaki Akeno aspire to become one of the Blue Mermaid. And so, she attended Yokosuka girls High school where she became the captain of the Harekaze with her classmates as her crew. Unfortunately, on their first day of school, they got attacked by their instructor's ship which forces them to defend themselves. In result, they are now hunted by authorities for mutiny. However, things are getting more complicated when many of their schools' ships also mutinied which is up to Misaki and her crew to get to the bottom of this incident while being on the run in this nautical adventure.

Name: 607. Shinzo
Description: n the world of Mushrambo, human life has all but come to an end. After a deadly virus threatened the extinction of mankind, a new race called the Enterrans was created to preserve life on Earth. However, relations between the Enterrans and their creators did not remain peaceful. Soon a war broke out with the Enterrans fighting against the humans and their robots. Ultimately the Enterrans were the victors of this conflict, renaming Earth as Enterra in honor of their victory. Before the last vestiges of humanity fell, one of the few remaining scientists put his daughter, Yakumo Shindou, into a sleep chamber. His hope was that his daughter would one day reawaken and find the human sanctuary known as Shinzo, reviving humanity and restoring peace between humans and Enterrans. Centuries have passed since the war; Yakumo now awakens and meets an Enterran named Mashura who pledges to assist in her quest. Also joined by the Enterrans Sago and Kutal, the group must now work to locate Yakumo's missing memories and locate Shinzo. But not every Enterran is as kind as Yakumo's new friends and some are prepared to commit any atrocity to prevent the return of humanity.

Name: 608. Do It Yourself!!
Description: High school girls working on DIY projects, as they struggle, fail, yet don't give up and see the projects through to their end. The story depicts the lives of those girls as they take the first step toward the future.

Name: 609. Tamagotchi!
Description: Follows the lives of Mametchi and his friends as they progress through each day in TamaTown.

Name: 610. Zensh√ª.
Description: Natsuko Hirose embarks on animation career. Her debut anime becomes a smash hit, sparking social phenomenon and earning her recognition as a brilliant emerging director.

Name: 611. Please Tell Me! Galko-chan
Description: Three teenage girls discuss subjects that are usually of an embarrassing nature. Their interactions are gently humorous and often informative.

Name: 612. Transformers: Go!
Description: Two teams of Autobots arrive on Earth with the mission of hunting down Predacons around the planet.

Name: 613. Oishinbo
Description: Oishinbo is a drama about newspaper reporters. The main character is a cynical food critic named Yamaoka.

Name: 614. Trinity Seven: Eternity Library & Alchemic Girl
Description: The film's story begins when Arata inadvertently touches "Hermes Apocrypha," Lilith's Grimoire. Suddenly, he is enveloped by a bright white light, and a girl appears before him. She calls herself Lilim, and treats both Arata and Lilith as her parents. At the same time she appears, something changes in the world. The forbidden Eternal Library awakens. In the Library is sealed the ultimate culmination of Alchemy, the White Demon Lord. The White Demon Lord plots to eliminate Arata and the Trinity Seven to usurp the position of Demon Lord. Bristling with untold power, the White Demon Lord attacks Arata, and triggers a desperate crisis where Arata and the Trinity Seven must save the world in this last battle.

Name: 615. Magic Boy
Description: A young Japanese boy climbs a mountain in search of a magic wizard. The youth finds the wizard, and is tutored by him. Reinforced with magic powers, the boy eventually fights and defeats the evil witches of down under.

Name: 616. BOA
Description: Official music video for "BOA" by Megan Thee Stallion.

Name: 617. Origin: Spirits of the Past
Description: It is 300 years into the future. Earth's environment had been devastated by mankind's own foolish plans and humankind is beleaguered by the sentient forests which they have awoken. The world balance is tipped when a young boy named Agito stumbles across a machine that glowed in a strange blue hue inside a forbidden sanctuary. The machine, which has preserved a beautiful girl named Tula from the past, is activated. Tula has a "mission" that had been entrusted to her by the past ...

Name: 618. Tokyo Majin
Description: A force of supernatural darkness is unleashing the walking dead on Tokyo, and five high school students with extraordinary powers - and nothing in common - must band together to fight the scourge.

Name: 619. Saki
Description: A tenth-former wore out an old acquaintance by name Saki Miyanaga in the school club of mahjong only because that knew rules, and for a game the fourth was not enough. Certainly, Saki nothing such did not show and, winning back three circles, moved away modestly. But only president of club Hisa Takei noticed that a guest all three meeting had made off "in a zero" - that a chance in any way can not be.

Name: 620. My Santa
Description: A teen boy named Santa was born on Christmas Eve who was abandoned doesn't believe in love, until he meets a girl named Mai who promises him the best Christmas ever!

Name: 621. Anime Abandon
Description: A philosophical masochist reviews Anime films of the most bizarre caliber, ranging from horrifically violent to borderline pornographic to just plain crazy.

Name: 622. Gundam Build Fighters Try
Description: Seven years after it's predecessor, Fumina Hoshino is the host of the Gunpla club in her high school, and, unfortunately, she is the only member and in danger of it being shut down. When a transfer student, Kamiki Sekai asks for the "fighting club", she takes him to the Gunpla club instead, he originally declines, but eventually they start fighting battles with their Gunpla, and from there on they start reaching for the top together.

Name: 623. Prince Planet
Description: Prince Planet was sent from his home planet Radion to study the people of Earth and help them in their fight against evil. His power comes from a pendant he wears, which can only be recharged by energy transmitted from Radion.

Name: 624. Pretty Rhythm: Aurora Dream
Description: Prism Stars are performers on the new popular ice show, Prism Show. They are super idols whose techniques, singing and fashion sense are a cut above all others. Aira and Rizumu are two Prism Stars whose goal is to become the best, the Prism Queen; however, the road to success is bumpy.

Name: 625. Kureyon Shinchan: Arashi o Yobu: Utau Ketsudake Bakudan!
Description: Rate

Name: 626. Orenchi no Furo Jijou
Description: A lonely man meets a handsome but homeless merman and brings him home to live with him in his bathtub.

Name: 627. AnimeTV
Description: TV Series

Name: 628. Bubu & Bubulina
Description: A mean older sister "BUBULINA" and a serious younger sister "BUBU". One day, a girl who had queerly long legs came before them. Her red shoes caught the eyes of BUBULINA. She said, "With the shoes, you can dance very well like this. Do you want to try?" "Yes!" BUBULINA strongly nodded her head. In the next instant, the red shoes held on to BUBULINA...!?

Name: 629. Ginga e Kickoff
Description: After his team was disbanded, Sho Ota is 6th grader determined on finding new members to reassemble the Momotaro Predators.

Name: 630. Marvel vs. Capcom: Clash of Super Heroes
Description: The evil Onslaught has become too powerful, so the Marvel universe is assisted by the Capcom universe to destroy him before he is unstoppable.

Name: 631. Eternights
Description: Eternights is a dating action game, blending a love story with adrenaline-driven combat as you make the most out of life during the apocalypse. Scavenge for supplies, explore dungeons - and go on dates.

Name: 632. Robotech: The Shadow Chronicles
Description: Picking up where the original series left off, Scott Bernard continues his search for Rick Hunter and the fate of the SDF-3.

Name: 633. The Dragon from Russia
Description: May Yip and Yao are both orphans and have been friends since youth, but they're torn apart when the leader of the 8 Hundred Dragons Kung Fu cult abducts Yao and erases his memory.

Name: 634. The Family Circumstances of the Irregular Witch
Description: The daily lives of a family of two witches, Alyssa and her daughter Viola.

Name: 635. My Last Day
Description: The Scriptural story unfolds through the eyes of a criminal who receives the same brutal crucifixion sentence as Jesus of Nazareth. It is a short moral film of regret, repentance and redemption.

Name: 636. Kemeko Deluxe!
Description: 6-year old Sanpeita Kobayashi got engaged to his childhood friend, a mysterious pink-haired girl who promised they would meet again 10 years later, and she would become his bride. The series begins then.

Name: 637. Adam Chaplin 2
Description: Adam allies with someone new to pursue revenge after defeating a demon. General Darrius Richards returns to Heaven Valley with cyber-soldiers to avenge his son's death. Violence between the parties is imminent.

Name: 638. RWBY Chibi
Description: A spinoff of the popular rooster teeth show RWBY. This show is small clips of the cast of RWBY in their spare time.

Name: 639. Take My Brother Away!
Description: Teenage siblings Fen and Shi Mao fight about everything every single day. However, when disaster strikes, they've got each other's backs. Hopefully.

Name: 640. Re: Zero kara hajimeru isekai seikatsu: Death or Kiss
Description: When Subaru Natsuki leaves the convenience store, the last thing he expects is to be wrenched from his everyday life and dropped into a fantasy world. Things aren't looking good for the bewildered teenager; however, not long after his arrival, he is attacked by some thugs. Armed with only a bag of groceries and a now useless cell phone, he is quickly beaten to a pulp. Fortunately, a mysterious beauty named Satella, in hot pursuit after the one who stole her insignia, happens upon Subaru and saves him. In order to thank the honest and kindhearted girl, Subaru offers to help in her search, and later that night, he even finds the whereabouts of that which she seeks. But unbeknownst to them, a much darker force stalks the pair from the shadows, and just minutes after locating the insignia, Subaru and Satella are brutally murdered.

Name: 641. Sophie and Virginia
Description: The two orphan sisters Sophie and Virginie travel around the world on different adventures.

Name: 642. Maximillian
Description: The secret team of assassins, the Shadows, are put to the test in an ultimate game of survival.

Name: 643. Otaku
Description: A documentary that explores the life styles of various otakus in Japan. Various interviews are given to selected otakus who express how interesting it is to be an otaku as oppose to not being one at all. Along with various shots of various Japanese city landscapes and the inside of an average otaku home from rooms filled with videos, models, and the latest in technology.

Name: 644. Samurai Harem
Description: When Yoichi moves from the mountains to the city, he'll go from surviving the wilderness to surviving with four fierce females.

Name: 645. Phantom of the Idol
Description: "Kami Kuzu Idol" is based upon the manga "Phantom of the Idol". Music promoters have paired two good looking boys to make the pop idol duo ZINGS. They have some problems though. The nice blond boy, Kazuki Yoshino, is hard working but lacks confidence. The dark moody boy, Yuuya Niyodo, only wants a lazy way to get rich. His manager is ready to fire him until - One evening Yuuya meets a pretty girl back stage, Asahi Mogami. She wants to work hard and be a successful idol. However she has a problem, she died a year ago. Her desire and Yuuya's laziness lead to an arrangement. Asahi possesses his body while working and he can be lazy the rest of the time.

Name: 646. The Murder of Sonic the Hedgehog
Description: Sonic the Hedgehog.. was murdered!? Get to the bottom of the mystery in this brand-new adventure.

Name: 647. Utawarerumono Mask of Truth
Description: Chaos has taken hold of the land in Mask of Truth as a conniving general has unlawfully seized the throne of the mighty Yamato Empire. The only ones that stand in his way are a couple of familiar faces who must rally different kingdoms together and fight against the powerful Imperial army.

Name: 648. Biohazard 4D: Executer
Description: In this non-canonical entry in the Resident Evil/Biohazard franchise, five members of the U.B.C.S. are sent to Racoon City to trace Dr. Cameron and, foremost, her research. However, the horrors they encounter are beyond their imagination.

Name: 649. Africa no Salaryman
Description: The comedy follows a lion, toucan, and lizard as they live the lives of office workers in a capitalist society in Japan, while also dealing with their unique situations as animals living beyond the savanna and the food chain.

Name: 650. Different Kinds of Rain
Description: A family struggles with the teenager son who suffers from Hikikomori phenomenon. Suddenly, he closes the door and locks himself in, shutting out a helpless father, mother and sister

Name: 651. The Lo0n
Description: The government says radiation has infested everything. The food we eat, the water we drink, the air we breathe. They've issued masks for everyone to wear when outside and anti-radiation medication is being distributed weekly around the world. People live in fear. Of everything, everyone. Some people don't believe the government, they think it's a conspiracy. But, Vincent, he just doesn't care. He doesn't wear a mask anywhere and sells his pills on the streets to the paranoid. Everyone thinks he's gone mad in the head.

Name: 652. Policenauts
Description: Johnathan Ingram is one of "policenauts" assigned the task of upholding the law on a space station called "Beyond Coast". Ingram was lost in the space after an accident left himn out of control in his spacesuit. But the suit was equipped with a cryogenic-life sistem and 25 year later his frozen body was recovered. The new world arround him is very different, all his friends are old men and his wife has remarried and had a daugther. Johnathan returns to the Earth and become in a private eye but when is ex-wife's new husband goes missing and she visiting Johnathan to ask for his help, Ingram returns to "Beyond Coast". Helped by is old friend Ed Brown, he will discover many things about is past and the tragic accident that changed his life...

Name: 653. Muse Dash
Description: Play as characteristic Heroines, Dash through fairy tale like stages, Dancing to the rhythm and beats, Kick those silly cute enemies into outer space.

Name: 654. Hirogaru Sky! Precure
Description: A major incident has occurred in the peaceful Sky Land!? The young Princess Eru has been kidnapped by the monsters of Underground Empire. A brave young girl, Sora, follows the princess through a mysterious hole. "TV"? "Cars"? Are those some kind of magic tools!?!? But there's no time to be surprised. She has to get the princess back to the castle.... Flying between two worlds. The adventure with the Pretty Cure begins now. It's hero time.

Name: 655. Atakku no. 1
Description: The series follows 12-year-old Ayuhara Kozue's hardships with a lung disease and her struggle in becoming a pro volleyball player.

Name: 656. Castlevania: Aria of Sorrow
Description: In the year 2035, Dracula's castle appears in modern Japan. High school student Soma Cruz teams up with Genya Arikado, Yoko Belnades and the amnesic "J" to defeat Graham Jones, who believes he is the new Dracula.

Name: 657. I Want You to Show Me Your Panties with a Disgusted Face 2
Description: A project where a number of women in different costumes show their panties while they make a disgusted face.

Name: 658. Enter the Anime
Description: It is a documentary special aimed at newcomers to anime, and follows anime newbie, Alex Burunova, as she dives into the mysterious world of the genre. The documentary features some of the biggest anime stars like Kenji Kamiyama, Shinji Aramaki, Kozo Morishita, production houses like TOEI Animation and Polygon Pictures and IP like Aggretsuko, Evangelion and Ultraman to give the fans a behind-the-scenes look at the elusive world of anime.

Name: 659. The Gene of AI
Description: A doctor who treats robot and humanoid problems takes place in the near future when humanoids with AI account for 10% of the population. Hikaru Sud√¥, also known as Moggadeet, secretly takes on illegal medical procedures.

Name: 660. The Idolm@ster
Description: The arduous struggle of the 13 girls from Talent Production 765 who dream of one day becoming idols in the competitive Japanese entertainment industry.

Name: 661. Pani poni dasshu!
Description: Rebecca Miyamoto, an 11-year-old child prodigy, accepts a teaching job at Momotsuki Gakuen (Peach Moon Academy), a high school that can be best described as 'bizarre'!

Name: 662. Date A Bullet: Nightmare or Queen
Description: Short

Name: 663. Afterimage
Description: Afterimage is a hand-drawn 2D action adventure that emphasizes fast-paced combat with diversified character builds, non-linear levels, and a gripping story set in the ruins of a fantasy world.

Name: 664. THE IDOLM@STER CINDERELLA GIRLS U149
Description: A spin-off of THE iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls set in a different canon, it features almost all of the younger idols under 12 years old (as the title implies, who are under 149cm in height) of the series and a new, short producer.

Name: 665. Mega Man 8
Description: A mysterious robot lands on Earth, along with a powerful substance, which Dr. Wily plans to harness to take over the world. Mega Man must stop him and discover who the mysterious robot is.

Name: 666. Hoshi no Samidare
Description: The world is in mortal peril. A high school boy has suddenly given a mission of finding the princess Samidare and protecting the planet from incredible "Biscuit Hammer".

Name: 667. Ai shite naito
Description: Love triangle between a girl from a traditional family and two members of a rock band.

Name: 668. Shin Yaranaika
Description: The story begins with Masaki Michishita, an ordinary prep school student who is rushing to the bathroom in a park one day. Despite his rush, he spots Takakazu Abe, an exceedingly handsome auto mechanic sitting on a bench. The two exchange looks, and after Abe utters "Yaranai ka" (Shall we do it?), the two begin their encounter.

Name: 669. Hurricane Polimar
Description: Takeshi Yoroi was trained for years as an officer of the International Secret Police Agency, including training in martial arts and several athletic skills. But his mentor distrusted his initiatives and eventually kicked him out of the force. Takeshi resurfaced as the assistant of the private detective Joe Kuruma. Secretly, Takeshi acquired a special suit with several different forms and weapons. He became the armored superhero Hurricane Polymar, engaging in a private war against organized crime.

Name: 670. Dark Cat
Description: Brothers Hyoi and Ryoi Kagezaki use their ability to shape-shift into cats to combat a malevolent influence at their school.

Name: 671. Tenchi Universe
Description: An alternate re-telling of 'Tenchi Muyo'.

Name: 672. Accel World: Infinite Burst
Description: Nega Nebulus investigates a disturbance in the Accelerated World which is also having negative effects on the real world, and is forced to team up with the other Kings to combat the threat.

Name: 673. Wenn sich Menschenblut mit Vampirblut vermischt
Description: The beginning was hard and dark. It wasn't always easy for me to get there. But I wouldn't want to change anything in the world. My experiences have made me who I am today. In fact, it was 18 years ago now. When your classmate Caraxia disappeared without a trace. A year later, she was officially declared dead. But her body would never be found. Suddenly she came back. She also brings another person with her, a vampire, and when human blood mixes with vampire blood, the story's path leads through the mysterious world of samurai and the dark world of vampires. A character that seemed to come from a deep black nightmare. But you can't wake up. Suddenly a vampire appears in the room. The mother's physical love and pride for her (Kalaxyja). Your beloved child. There is no second chance for the first impression. "Oh my god - vampire" was the first impression.For most people it is the sight that presents itself to them,like a deep black nightmare,You just want to wake up from it.He is not ugly at all.But a 17-year-old boy with sharp teeth and claws,Eyes glowing in the dark,Wearing a black silk kimono. And a sword in his hand.It can be scary.

Name: 674. Dream Fighter Wingman
Description: A big superhero fan, Kenta created his own character: Wingman. However, his pranks tend to irritate his teachers as well as his junior high school sweetheart, the lovely Miku. The middle-schooler is overwhelmed when the beautiful Aoi irrupts into his life. Travelling from a parallel world, she grants him the protection of the Dream Notes, a book which can bring to life anything that is written in it. Every wild idea is now at the tip of Kenya's pencil... Wingman can now come to life to help Aoi protect the precious book from the evil Rimel! Wingman is one of the first successes from famous mangaka Masakazu Katsura (I"s, Video Girl Ai, DNA2, Zetman), that quickly got adapted for television by Toei Animation.
